  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-03-26",
    "date": "2021-09-01T20:55:08Z",
    "text": "Rural Behavioral Health Access Act of 2021\n\nThis bill allows for Medicare payment of outpatient critical access hospital (CAH) services consisting of telehealth behavioral therapy, including (1) audio-only services, if an individual does not have access to technology with both audio and visual capabilities; and (2) services provided to an individual who has not received in-person care at the CAH, if there is a plan of care that includes an in-person visit not later than one year after telehealth services are provided."
  },
